removeWhiteList(address).details: Implementation of revoke an invalid address from the whitelist.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.denominator: thedenominator of transaction fee. transaction fee = numerator/denominator;

subUserInputCollateral(address,address,u.details: Substract user's collateral balance. Only manager contract can modify database.

subUserPayingUsd(address,uint256).details: Substract user paying data,priced in USD. Only manager contract can modify database.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

transferPayback(address,address,uint256).details: Operation for transfer user's payback. Only manager contract can invoke this function.

transferPaybackAndFee(address,address,ui.details: Operation for transfer user's payback and deduct transaction fee. Only manager contract can invoke this function.

params.feeType: the transaction fee type. see transactionFee contract

params.colBalances: the Collateral balance based for user's input collateral.
params.redeemWorth: the redeem worth, priced in USD.
